  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Season the <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680174989968-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680174989968-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680174989968-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680174989968-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680174989968-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a matching lid with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>diced</strong> <strong>beef</strong> to the dish and cook for 3-4 min or until browned all over, then remove from the dish and set aside, reserve the dish</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680174994394-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680174994394-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680174994394-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680174994394-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680174994394-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the beef is browning, peel and quarter the <strong>shallots</strong></p><p>Crush the <strong>garlic</strong> open by squashing them with the side of a knife and discard the skins</p><p>Top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680174999601-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680174999601-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680174999601-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680174999601-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680174999601-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the dish to a medium-high heat and once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>shallots</strong>, <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until browned</p><p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>red wine paste</strong> and <strong>tomato</strong> <strong>paste</strong> in 475ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>red wine stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680175003541-x200.jpg",
