            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680175003541-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680175003541-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have browned, return the <strong>browned beef </strong>to the dish with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>red wine stock</strong>, <strong>bay</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> and <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover the dish with a lid and put in the oven for 1 hour or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through – this is your <strong>beef bourguignon</strong></p>",
